contract_type.raw_snippet:
TECHNOLOGY OUTSOURCING AGREEMENT
This Master Agreement is made as of the 26 day of January, 2007 (the “Effective Date”), by and between Oriental Financial Group
Inc., a Puerto Rico financial holding company (“Customer”), and Metavante Corporation, a Wisconsin corporation (“Metavante”).
Customer desires Metavante to provide to Customer the services and licenses as set forth in this Agreement and its amendments, and
Metavante desires to provide such services and licenses to Customer, all as provided in this Agreement and its amendments.
contract_type.reasoning: The title and the substantive recitals make clear the core transaction: Metavante will provide technology services and software/licenses to Customer. The contract governs provision of services, conversion, licenses, ongoing operations and support—i.e., outsourcing of technology and processing services. Therefore the primary type is an Outsourcing Agreement.

notice_period.raw_snippet:
Unless this Agreement has been earlier terminated, Metavante shall provide a written renewal notice to Customer at least
twelve (12) months prior to the expiration of the Initial Term (the “Renewal Notice”). Unless Customer notifies Metavante of its intent not
to renew this Agreement in writing within a period of three (3) months following the Renewal Notice, this Agreement shall automatically
renew at the end of the Initial Term on the same terms (including pricing terms) for one (1) twelve-month period.
notice_period.reasoning: This paragraph in Section 2.1 sets out the renewal-notice process and specifically prescribes the timeframe in which Customer must give written notice to avoid automatic renewal: within three (3) months following Metavante's Renewal Notice (which Metavante must give at least 12 months prior to expiration). The requested field concerns the advance notice required to prevent automatic renewal, which is the three-month period specified for Customer to notify Metavante after receipt of the Renewal Notice.
notice_period.normalized_value: 3 months (within three (3) months following the Renewal Notice)

expiration_date.raw_snippet: The term of this Agreement shall commence on the Effective Date and end on November 30, 2014 (the “Initial Term”).
expiration_date.reasoning: This clause explicitly states the contract term end date as a calendar date (the Initial Term ends on November 30, 2014). Because an exact calendar date is provided, the normalized value is returned as an ISO date.
